The starry sky has about the Gemini meteor shower on the 14 th-Xinhuanet Xinhua Agency, Tianjin, December 12(Reporter Zhou Runjian) Astronomical science experts said that as the last large-scale meteor shower of the year, the Geminid meteor shower, one of the three major meteor showers in the North hemisphere, will usher in a great event on December 14. Friends who like meteor showers can observe it in the middle of the night.But the Geminid meteor shower 's parent body is asteroid 3200 Phaethon, an Apollo-type asteroid. The Geminid meteor shower is also the second known meteor shower that is not "spawned" by a comet. Tianjin City Astronomical Society director, Astronomical science expert Xiu Lipeng said, Like the New Year blockbuster, The geminids meteor shower generally appear at the end of the year,"Release schedule" Can last from December 4 to 17. The meteor shower to flow large and stable known, And quadrant meteor shower, Perseid meteor shower together known as the North hemisphere three major meteor shower. A notable feature of the geminids meteor shower is the slow speed of meteoroids, rich color, bolide also many,This year 's Geminid meteor shower will be at its maximum at around 15:00 on December 14, with a ZHR of 150 (the number of meteors seen per hour when the radiant point is directly above the head under ideal observation conditions). Geminid meteor shower recommended index chart."Last year, the 'falling petals' of the Geminid meteor shower left a deep impression on people, but this year's Geminid meteor shower will be disturbed by moonlight, and the degree of excitement will be a little discounted. The 14th is the 11th day of the 11th lunar month, and the moon phase is a full convex moon. The bright moonlight will interfere with the observation. Fortunately, the moon will fall in the middle of the night.At this time, the radiant point of the Geminids meteor shower will also rise higher. Friends who like meteor showers can observe them in the last few hours of the night after the moon, but be careful to keep warm."How can we observe as many meteors as possible?" "It is not recommended to observe in the city. You can choose a place with a high altitude, low light damage and a wide field of vision facing the northeast in the suburbs or countryside, and then wait patiently until the moon sets and observe it visually. It should be noted that the flow of the Gemini meteor shower in all directions is very large, so you don't have to stare at the radiant point of the Gemini meteor shower all the time. If you like photography, you want to shoot a gorgeous 'meteor shower blockbuster', it is best to choose a wide angle,For large-aperture lenses, use high ISO and maximum aperture when shooting. For stability and continuity, a tripod, backup battery and shutter release are also essential,"Xiu Lipeng warned.
